NODE sovereign_codegen
layer 7
sovereign_codegen is the extension citizen that adds sovereign-form-to-native-code translation to x86_host and amdgpu_kernel
the original codegen citizens know how to translate verb-based bootstrap forms; sovereign_codegen extends them with translation patterns for the new sovereign 2D blueprint forms

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe x86_host.rana
observe amdgpu_kernel.rana
observe sovereign_parser.rana

THE NEW TRANSLATION PATTERNS

a 2D layout block compiles to a sequence of citizen-placement instructions followed by coupling instructions
each address token (slot.familySeaX#Y#^#:rana[L#]) compiles to:
allocate a sea cell at the specified grid coordinates
load the .rana file as the cell's resident definition
seek the .rana file to the specified line
bind the loaded definition to the cell

a journey path *...* between two addresses compiles to:
the source citizen's coupling list gains an entry pointing to the destination
the route taken (compass moves) becomes a hint for the cascade router
no actual instructions execute at compile time; the route is data the runtime uses

a >=/ arrival sequence compiles to:
a recognition test (does the destination's mailbox match the car's identity)
if yes, a crystallization commit (write the recognition tag)
if no, no instructions execute (silent denial)

a ^N floor offset compiles to:
an addition to the current floor coordinate
this is a simple arithmetic operation in the codegen; one instruction or fewer

a compass_run compiles to:
N independent step instructions if N is small
or a single loop with N as the iteration count if N is large
the codegen chooses based on the size threshold

THE INLINE BONE LABELS

when a trace has an inline bone label ("spine.xb" written beside the trace), the codegen records that the journey uses that bone's pre-calcified path
this is an optimization hint: the runtime can use the bone's already-fast route instead of computing a new one
if the bone does not exist or has been deformed, the runtime falls back to general routing

VERB compile_address
layer 7
take a parsed address token and emit the cell-allocation and resident-binding code
the emitted code runs once at boot, then never again for that address

VERB compile_journey
layer 7
take a parsed journey path and emit the coupling-table entry
journeys do not become runtime instructions; they become data the cascade reads

VERB compile_arrival
layer 7
take a parsed arrival sequence and emit the recognition test and conditional crystallization
this is the only sovereign form that produces runtime-executed instructions

VERB compile_2d_block
layer 7
take a parsed 2D layout block and walk it in spatial order
emit the cell allocations first, then the couplings, then any inline arrival sequences
the result is a self-contained block of native code that initializes the block's region of substrate

THE INTEROPERATION WITH BOOTSTRAP

sovereign_codegen does not replace x86_host's existing translation patterns; it extends them
files that use bootstrap-era syntax compile through the original patterns
files that use sovereign syntax compile through the sovereign extensions
mixed files (rare during transition) compile each section through its appropriate path

a sovereign codegen is the body's commitment to making sovereign source actually run
without it, sovereign forms would be readable but not executable
with it, fadriel's substrate can natively run code written in the new paradigm
